job_lists.content:
The "Android System Engineer" will be based in Shanghai ZhangJiang. 
Flex's AR/VR Engineering team is seeking an experienced engineer for next generation AR/VR products development, you will have the opportunity to create great user experience improvements with new technologies, and involve working on the full cycle of product development required to bring the product successfully to market.

Here is a glimpse of what you'll do…
• Responsible for Android system development and integration;
• Take part in Android system software bug fix and optimization;
• Advanced research and evaluation of new technologies.

Here is some of what you'll need (required)…
• Bachelor or higher degree, excellent C/C++ programming skills;
• More than 5 years of Android/Linux development experience;
• Strong knowledge of Android peripherals driver development and debugging;
• Experienced in leading Android system software development;
• Familiar with digital communication protocols, e.g., I2C, I2S, SPI, UART, USB, SDIO, MIPI;
• Familiar with Android system framework, mechanism and core services;
• Familiar with Android graphic framework, OpenGL development experience is preferred;
• Android Multimedia/Sensor framework development experience is preferred;
• Able to communicate in English F2F, working experience in English environment.

Here are a few of our preferred experiences…
• Experiences in AR/VR product development is preferred;
• Experiences in Qualcomm platform is preferred.

We are looking for someone who demonstrates:
• Intense collaboration;
• Passionate customer focus;
• Thoughtful, fast, disciplined execution;
• Tenacious commitment to continuous improvement;
• Willing to study new technology, communicate & cooperate;
• Relentless drive to win.
